About this item

  • CREATE AN ELEGANT AMBIANCE - set the mood for dinner, dim the lights to create a movie theatre experience, turn the lights down low to wind down for bedtime
  • PERSONALIZE YOUR LIGHTING - customizable fade rates that gradually turn lighting on or off, or preset light level options to make sure lights always come on at the level you want
  • AUTOMATIC SOFTER LIGHTING AT NIGHT - perfect in your kitchen for a midnight snack or in your bathroom, using My Leviton Night Settings
  • PREVENT FLICKERING LIGHTS - designed for compatibility with dimmable LED bulbs and fixtures with settings to fine-tune performance such as bulb type, min dim, and max bright
  • USE YOUR VOICE FOR CONTROL WITHOUT LIGHTING A FINGER - works with Google Assistant, Amazon Alexa, and Apple Siri
  • THE MOST CONNECTED - Matter support can be enabled with a firmware update via the My Leviton app
  • KNOW IF LIGHTS ARE ON AND ADJUST WHETHER YOU'RE HOME, AT WORK, OR ON VACATION - control from anywhere
  • ONE SWITCH, MANY OPTIONS - use as a dimmer switch (rated for 300W dimmable LED or CFL; 600W Incadescent, or 600VA MLV) or as an on/off switch via non-dimmable bulb mode
  • SINGLE POLE OR 3-WAY - control this dimmer from another wall location in your home; works with DD00R / DD0SR Wired Companions or use DAWDC / DAWSC Anywhere Companions with no additional wiring needed
  • EASY INSTALL - replaces your existing switch (no hub required); wire leads and slim design make install a breeze, fast guided setup with the My Leviton app

      Product Description

      Decora Smart Wi-Fi 2nd Gen devices connect to a Wi-Fi network and the My Leviton app to provide wireless lighting control for the whole home with no hub required. Levitons Wi-Fi 2nd Gen Dimmer makes it easier than ever to add smart lighting control possibilities to any room or home. Connect locally to any Matter enabled Smart Home platform of your choice. Use your voice with Hey Google, Amazon Alexa or Apple Siri to dim and brighten connected lighting. Use the My Leviton app on a smartphone, tablet, or computer to control lighting or adjust schedules. Decora Smart dimmers feature full range dimming performance and custom settings for preset light levels, fade rates, and bulb types. Add optional wire-free 3-way/multi-location where you need it, simply pair with wireless DAWDC Anywhere Dimmer Companions or DAWSC Anywhere Switch Companions (no wiring required). Rated for dimmable LED and CFL loads up to 300-Watt or incandescent and MLV loads up to 600-Watt, neutral wire required with a 2-year limited warranty. Decora Smart Wi-Fi 2nd Gen devices operate on 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi networks. The Decora Smart Wi-Fi Dimmer can be combined with other Decora Smart Wi-Fi devices to create a Whole Home experience with scheduling, lighting scenes, and app control from anywhere. Go beyond a single device by adding switches, fan speed controllers, outlets, and more to control all lights, ceiling fans, electronics, and small appliances. Vanishing LEDs, color change faceplates and wallplates ensure the switch matches the aesthetic of all other smart and non-smart Decora devices in the home.

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      • WA Driver
        4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to wire - Matter readiness requires firmware update
        Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2024
        Verified Purchase
        It was simple to wire. Do make sure you have neutral in the box before buying! Recommend down loading the Leviton App ASAP so you can get into the Matter upgrade program. The firmware in the switches currently shipping don't support Matter. Once you have the switch up on your home network (following Leviton directions) go to device settings and Check for Firmware Update Current version supporting Matter is 2.1.25. Once upgraded a new menu item "Matter Pairing Code" will appear. Click this and write down the 11-digit code. The go to the switch and hold the top paddle for 7 seconds to put the switch in Pairing Mode (flashing green led). Go to your hub controller and add the new Matter device using the require procedure for your hub and the 11-digit Matter Pairing code. Let me add that I contacted the Leviton support, and they did their best to support me. Now that I know the process I may buy this switch again - but first it has to pass my break in and reliability tests.
        Read more
